Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.96,0:01:41.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Lawrence going to be alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.66,0:01:43.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite frankly, it'll probably be tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.91,0:01:47.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt he'll be able to compete effectively with so little pyrite.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.74,0:01:51.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do is pray that Deanna's assistant comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.79,0:01:54.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If he sells a superficial amount,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.64,0:02:00.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,all it'll do is get people's hopes up that there's more to buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.89,0:02:03.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And if that happens, the price will just rise even higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.66,0:02:11.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that mean Amarty can pretend he's about to sell in order to bait Lawrence?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.29,0:02:12.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.73,0:02:14.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.58,0:02:24.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Horo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:39.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a fool that gets agitated easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.51,0:02:42.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You can just relax. {Work calmly? hmm...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.51,0:02:43.55,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Horo...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:44.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Amarty... {主様 <- decide how we will translate this.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.51,0:02:46.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.77,0:02:48.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Another buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.23,0:02:51.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how much will it rise?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:57.65,main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&H575F66&\4c&H575F66&\pos(640,504)\blur3\1c&HCCD4DD&}Wolf and Trustworthy God
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.49,0:03:01.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gone up that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:05.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing it'll go up another 20% by this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:08.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I had bought more of it instead of giving up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.66,0:03:11.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still slowly rising in value, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:18.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember right, Amarty currently has 800 silver worth of pyrite.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.38,0:03:19.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And when it goes up another 20%?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.88,0:03:22.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be 960 coins worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:25.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If that happens, he'll sell his assets on the spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:28.56,main,,0000,0000,0000,,scrape around for the remaining 40 coins,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:31.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,and definitively seal the contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.06,0:03:34.61,main,,0000,0000,0000,,All before the poison of selling on credit takes effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.48,0:03:37.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The poison of selling on credit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.28,0:03:38.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Still nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.57,0:03:41.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Deanna's assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.07,0:03:48.45,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If she's been with Amarty this whole time, Horo may have attained quite a lot of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.45,0:03:49.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.79,0:03:55.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.67,0:03:57.42,main,,0000,0000,0000,,To think it'd come this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.42,0:03:59.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it'll still go up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.51,0:04:01.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad...{That's right, MAZUI!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.84,0:04:05.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who made a deal with Deanna must have been Amarty after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:06.39,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.39,0:04:10.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,even if Amarty wins, Lawrence gets paid, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:12.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.23,0:04:15.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So as a merchant, it would be a win for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:17.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's also a huge loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.19,0:04:22.45,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Because no matter how much he pays, he'll never be able to buy it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.20,0:04:25.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Pyrite?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.57,0:04:29.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you after the alchemists' stockpile?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.74,0:04:32.91,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you make the contract after finding a buyer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.62,0:04:36.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately I didn't have the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.33,0:04:39.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone has already bought some.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.67,0:04:41.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll handle the negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:46.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where will I be able to contact you tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.59,0:04:49.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of the mineral merchant's stall at the marketplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.64,0:04:56.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No good, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.61,0:05:02.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Another buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.36,0:05:09.66,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to trade me for 1000 silver, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.66,0:05:10.87,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.30,0:05:25.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,He's looking for her as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.47,0:05:26.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A sale!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:30.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Amarty?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.56,0:05:33.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:35.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me through please!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.61,0:05:45.69,main,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:49.49,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.49,0:05:51.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Another buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:53.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.29,0:05:56.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are things going to start moving now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.71,0:05:58.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Time to sell?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.17,0:06:00.00,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, buying's still the way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:07.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Horo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.26,0:06:09.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.93,0:06:11.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:16.52,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a patron at the store saying he'd like to pay for barley in stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.52,0:06:17.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:19.52,main,,0000,0000,0000,,250 coins worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.40,0:06:22.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Be as quick as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.69,0:06:24.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.44,0:06:28.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,A sale!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:30.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I need this to rise more.{as if you get to choose this stuff, ossan!!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.88,0:06:47.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Amarty bought 500 coins worth of pyrite from Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.80,0:06:51.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Not in real goods, but with a certificate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:55.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The goods change hands this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.22,0:06:58.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.61,0:07:08.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If the price looks like it'll rise, the certificate will sell,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:12.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,but if the price looks like it'll drop, it probably won't sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.36,0:07:13.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.95,0:07:16.37,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody would deal in something so dangerous. {a dangerous thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.74,0:07:20.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If the pyrite returns to its original value as a rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.71,0:07:23.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,the 500 silver certificate becomes as worthless as garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:27.00,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The person with the certificate at the end loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:27.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:30.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the poison of buying on credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:42.39,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Horo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.39,0:07:43.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Horo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.11,0:07:51.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, Lanto.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.07,0:07:51.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Another purchase!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.11,0:07:54.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,An ore purchase!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.03,0:07:56.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.20,0:07:59.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And there are fewer waiting to buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:02.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I sold all I have now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.04,0:08:08.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm selling!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:29.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had that 400 silver worth of pyrite from Deanna...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.02,0:08:31.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,the winds would definitely blow my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:34.15,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If she came now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.15,0:08:36.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Lawrence!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:41.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for taking so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:44.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,250 silver of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.46,0:08:48.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.34,0:08:49.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:55.63,main,,0000,0000,0000,,To be perfectly safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.63,0:08:58.18,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I should wait for Deanna's assistant...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.18,0:08:59.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:01.27,main,,0000,0000,0000,,will she come?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.27,0:09:02.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.89,0:09:06.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:08.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd only just given up on that chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.31,0:09:11.23,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm going to take this gamble...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.98,0:09:13.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's my only chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.62,0:09:33.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:34.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone placed an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:38.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The winds have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.81,0:09:41.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice but to wait for Deanna's assistant now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:43.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Amarty!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.36,0:09:47.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he discover the poison behind the credit?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.30,0:09:49.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,She'll come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.48,0:09:50.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure she'll come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.37,0:09:53.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time, regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.54,0:09:55.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.72,0:09:56.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.94,0:09:57.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.73,0:09:59.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Lawrence?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.83,0:10:07.62,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You are Lawrence, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:09.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.71,0:10:12.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I bring a message from Deanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.63,0:10:14.84,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.38,0:10:18.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Negotiations have failed."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.01,0:10:21.14,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"They weren't willing to sell after all."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.14,0:10:22.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That is Deanna's message.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.51,0:10:26.43,main,,0000,0000,0000,,She apologizes for not meeting your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.52,0:10:31.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.49,0:10:44.16,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking for you, Horo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:50.29,main,,0000,0000,0000,,...rence... {can't sub it like this, can we? :/}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.29,0:10:51.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:53.00,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:54.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.38,0:10:57.21,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.21,0:10:58.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.13,0:11:00.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I put you through a lot of hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.55,0:11:04.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you pass this onto Mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.43,0:11:07.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him the plan failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:09.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:11.81,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I do get 1000 silver coins from Amarty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.81,0:11:14.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,As a merchant I should be delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.32,0:11:17.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now here's your share.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.07,0:11:18.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence!!!{shut the fuck up kid ><}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:21.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you giving up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.07,0:11:27.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The master always tells me that merchants should never give up easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:31.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The god of wealth doesn't come to those who pray,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:34.08,main,,0000,0000,0000,,but to those who don't know when to give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.84,0:11:36.59,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was told if I said this to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.71,0:11:41.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be beaten to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:42.22,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll say it! {HIT HIM!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.30,0:11:44.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've felt it since I first saw her!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.60,0:11:47.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I LOVE HORO!{yeah, we all do, get out the way.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.90,0:11:54.98,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.98,0:11:57.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, I do want lay down a beating.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:02.82,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to beat...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.28,0:12:04.49,main,,0000,0000,0000,,myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:07.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.58,0:12:12.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,People who don't give up are the kind who realize things that nobody else believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:15.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.92,0:12:21.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Merchants make a plan, theorize an outcome, and compare it with reality when doing trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.72,0:12:23.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I buy this, the outcome will be like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.55,0:12:25.30,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I sell this, the outcome will be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:27.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That kind of theory is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.56,0:12:32.39,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, there are any number of theories you could come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.89,0:12:36.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why if you speculate too much, you'll soon become lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.19,0:12:40.90,main,,0000,0000,0000,,All types of trade will start to seem very risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:45.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So in order not to become lost, we keep a guidepost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.61,0:12:48.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the one thing a merchant requires.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.03,0:12:54.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If that guidepost is trustworthy, we should take even the craziest ideas,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.67,0:12:58.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,and maybe just believe in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.22,0:13:07.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I sell the stones, spread that rumor I asked you to please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.30,0:13:10.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.77,0:13:15.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe in God?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.03,0:13:27.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You came again, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.28,0:13:30.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm selling.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.87,0:13:36.71,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm selling too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.79,0:13:38.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:40.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:44.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike someone I know, that woman was quite a mature beauty, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.11,0:14:12.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, Amarty didn't make that much of a loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.03,0:14:14.58,main,,0000,0000,0000,,The mental blow was far greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.58,0:14:17.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your punishment for trying to steal someone else's woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.87,0:14:19.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what happened after.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.88,0:14:23.50,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to leave him in a poorer state than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.88,0:14:26.34,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forgive that guy for what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.63,0:14:28.93,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.89,0:14:31.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.89,0:14:32.68,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.18,0:14:36.64,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you don't think that settles all of this, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.64,0:14:37.85,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.85,0:14:40.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really understand where you went wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.44,0:14:41.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.90,0:14:42.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.32,0:14:47.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,...probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:54.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Taking matters into my own hands after Amarty made that contract with you was completely arrogant of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.79,0:14:55.54,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.12,0:14:59.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My biggest mistake was not trusting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:05.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Those white feathers were supposed to be a sign that you were the one who'd bought the pyrite from Deanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:12.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But in my panic, when I saw Amarty go talk to the vendor, I thought it was a trap you had laid for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.97,0:15:16.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?{Norg: Try explaining that one!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.35,0:15:17.52,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.52,0:15:19.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were maybe trying to get me to sell prematurely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.48,0:15:24.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I really thought you had completely gone over to his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.40,0:15:28.24,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But... I guess I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.11,0:15:33.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You were trying to tell me that Amarty already had enough, so I should sell quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.45,0:15:37.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was confused and overthinking everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.91,0:15:39.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And before that, with the marriage certificate...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.25,0:15:42.00,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You signed your name on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.67,0:15:45.79,main,,0000,0000,0000,,but that was just to get me angry enough to confront you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.67,0:15:48.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.76,0:15:52.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then I was waiting there on the second fl...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.59,0:15:54.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.93,0:15:55.97,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.85,0:15:59.72,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You once said in Rubinhaigen,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.77,0:16:03.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Don't beat around the bush."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.48,0:16:05.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Come out with what you truly feel."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.73,0:16:08.28,main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Problems are solved much faster if you yell at each other."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.98,0:16:12.07,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I misunderstood you from the start. {check plox} { !!! COMMENT BY FOTC: It's good. }
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.07,0:16:15.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When you got confused over Yoitsu,{Norg: confused -> upset}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:16.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,the last thing you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.83,0:16:18.83,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.79,0:16:22.33,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were rejecting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.87,0:16:24.17,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But, in truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:27.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,that was you coming to your senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.59,0:16:29.67,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.67,0:16:31.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.09,0:16:34.09,main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is exactly what they mean when they say it's hard to tell a poor thinker from a sleeping one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.09,0:16:37.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Not only did you ruin the plan I painstakingly put together,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.43,0:16:40.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,but you also thought I was treating you as my enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:44.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of that, you just couldn't let go of the deal with that kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:49.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that we only met recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.44,0:16:53.99,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I didn't think the bond we had was so shallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.57,0:16:57.37,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that just my wishful thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.83,0:17:00.45,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you really...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.71,0:17:05.87,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to continue traveling with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.05,0:17:16.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,My life until now has been all about business.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.89,0:17:18.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,And I intend to keep it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.35,0:17:20.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.31,0:17:23.60,main,,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to life outside business, think of me as a bit of a slow guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.98,0:17:29.11,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I want to travel with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:30.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.23,0:17:32.73,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.49,0:17:36.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't express it in words.{強いて言えば　俺のハチミツ漬けリンゴ　かな？}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:39.20,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of dry line is that? { !!! COMMENT BY FOTC: I would do away with the "lame". }
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.70,0:17:42.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You like dried jerky, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.95,0:17:44.16,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate it. {that looks like it hurt} { !!! COMMENT BY FOTC: I'd take it gladly. Getting bitten by Horo = LOVE. }{Norg: there are some acts where you really wouldn't want her to bite like that}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.21,0:17:48.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.92,0:17:54.38,main,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you persuade Deanna to sell you the pyrite?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.18,0:18:07.85,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I more or less figured out your plan from everything Amarty told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.85,0:18:10.94,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I must say I was impressed by what you came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.36,0:18:14.44,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you called her Deanna, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.86,0:18:17.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I actually went there for a different purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.28,0:18:19.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,For a different purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:22.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be better to say for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.49,0:18:25.95,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I found her house from the scent on the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.75,0:18:30.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, the place carried a strong stink like you'd find near hot springs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.50,0:18:33.46,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet that was harsh for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.05,0:18:42.10,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked her to make up a story that Yoitsu is still around somewhere, and pass it onto you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:50.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But all that woman did was get all the facts she could out of me and ignore my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.31,0:18:52.48,main,,0000,0000,0000,,That so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.98,0:18:59.36,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I'd finished embarrassing myself explaining the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.36,0:19:00.53,main,,0000,0000,0000,,you showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.20,0:19:03.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is anyone in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.16,0:19:05.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, that damn woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.33,0:19:08.75,main,,0000,0000,0000,,She came up with her own plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.83,0:19:14.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,She decided it would be a good idea to test your resolve, as if she knew it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.63,0:19:17.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why she said that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.92,0:19:19.01,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.51,0:19:23.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I also heard every word of your stupid question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:27.89,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any legends of pagan gods and humans becoming mates?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.14,0:19:30.02,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.56,0:19:38.74,main,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems there are a lot of these stories of humans and gods mating.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.74,0:19:42.03,main,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's how you feel, then I don't mind, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.99,0:19:44.41,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be gentle to me? {Norg: <33333333333333333333333333}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.12,0:19:47.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.83,0:19:51.04,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not in the mood after talking to that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:56.88,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice she isn't human?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.88,0:19:58.05,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.84,0:20:01.51,main,,0000,0000,0000,,There were lots of feathers scattered around the room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:03.47,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.76,0:20:07.31,main,,0000,0000,0000,,She's actually a bird bigger than you.{Norg: I guess this is a way of saying out of your league?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:14.35,main,,0000,0000,0000,,She fell for a traveling priest, and spent a long time with him working to build a church.{Norg: I don't get what きょうかいを作る is meant to mean.. so check this line please xD}{It means what it says, build a church -.-}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.35,0:20:18.40,main,,0000,0000,0000,,But the priest grew suspicious of her since she never grew old no matter how much time passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.69,0:20:21.19,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You can guess what happened afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.12,0:20:32.12,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to return to my homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.37,0:20:35.96,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's no longer there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.71,0:20:42.13,main,,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do when we arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.43,0:21:28.80,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Humans do some amazing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.80,0:21:31.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.35,0:21:36.06,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't mind if you were as fiery as that doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.10,0:21:40.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll manage somehow when I get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.82,0:21:44.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's going to take care of me if you get drunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.99,0:21:46.57,main,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.40,0:23:52.78,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode: Wolf and Playful Days
